Bug ID:021
Title: 21.Updating price to single digit fits more than 2.
Description: When you update the price of 2 or more location to a 1 digit price it fits more than 2 locations on 1 row.

Steps to Reproduce:
Step 1: Open browser and go to (https://lzcbvwog.acmebooking.com/).
Step 2: Log into your account.
Step 3: Click on Update price in the navbar(https://lzcbvwog.acmebooking.com/prices).
Step 4: Change the price on 2 locations to a single digit number.
Step 5: Affirm that you now have 3 locations on a single row.

Expected Result:
The system should only list 2 locations on 1 row regardless of how many digits the price has.
Actual Result:
You can squeeze 3 locations in 1 row when you change the price to a single digit.

Severity:
Low  

Priority:
Low

Additional Information:
-

Environment:
Browser: Brave 1.70.119, Mozilla Firefox 130.0.1 (64-bit)
Operating System: Windows 10, Windows 11
Device: Desktop PC
Network:Ethernet
